### 3. JWT Refresh Tokens & Logout Fixes
- Added `POST /api/auth/refresh` for rotating access tokens using a 7-day `refreshToken` cookie.
- Decreased `token` lifespan to 15 minutes for better security.
- Updated `POST /api/auth/logout` to clear both cookies without requiring Redis.

### 4. Cloudinary & Secure File Uploads
- Integrated `cloudinary` and `multer-storage-cloudinary` to directly upload product and profile images to the cloud.
- Replaced the local `uploads/` directory static route and updated file handlers to validate mime types and file sizes (5MB limit).
- Updated controllers (`vendorProductController`, etc.) to parse and save the secure cloud URL instead of local paths.

### 5. API Rate Limiting
- Added `express-rate-limit` middleware globally to `/api/` paths with a limit of 100 requests per minute to prevent abuse.
- Set stricter limits on `/register` and `/login` (5 requests per minute).

### 6. Product Existence Checks
- Validated `product.isDeleted` status inside the `wishlist` and `cart` controllers. Products that are soft-deleted or completely removed will return a `404 Product not found`.

### 7. Commission Audit Logs
- Created a dedicated `AuditLog` model to track commission rate changes applied by administrators.
- Logged changes natively in `adminVendorController` indicating `adminId`, `targetId`, and the before/after commission states.
- Implemented `GET /api/admin/audit-logs` (mounted at `/api/admin/audit-logs`) to retrieve recent administrative actions.

### 8. Soft Deletes
- Added `isDeleted` and `deletedAt` flags to `Product`, `VendorProduct`, and `User` models.
- Modified native MongoDB deletion operations (`deleteOne`, `findByIdAndDelete`) in controllers to use `findByIdAndUpdate` for soft deletions.
- Applied Mongoose `.pre(/^find/)` middleware on these schemas to automatically filter out soft-deleted documents from all queries.

### 9. Email Notification System
- Configured a basic SMTP `nodemailer` service inside `services/emailService.js` to dispatch emails asynchronously (without needing a Redis message queue).
- Connected a "Welcome Email" sequence on new user registration inside `auth.js`.
- Expanded Auth routes to include `/forgot-password` and `/reset-password` capabilities.
